<text>The Charging Tool

&lt; Previous | Index | Next &gt;

There are two buttons for the Charging Tool. One adds a positive charge (0.5 e by default) on a particle. The other adds a negative charge (-0.5 e by default) on a particle.

To charge a particle, first click on one of the buttons, and then click on the particle.

 
Tip: The functionalities of these two Charging Tool buttons are interconvertible: If you hold down the SHIFT key, a charge of oppostive sign will be added. For example, if you select the &quot;Add Positive Charge&quot; button but you hold down the SHIFT key, an amount of charge will be substracted.
 

You may practice with the Charging Tool in the following model:

 
[This is an embedded simulator.]

You will immediately see the effect of electrostatic forces when you run the model after charging some particles.

Script support

The charge command can be used to charge the selected particles with a speficied value of charge. Another method is to use the set command: set particle[i].charge [value], where i is the index of the particle. Combined with the select and loop command, the task of charging a set of particles with different values can be automated.

